@startuml Signal Stream Layout
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
title Signal Stream - System Overview

rectangle "Source Data" as Service {
  folder "Industrial Protocols" {
    [OPC UA]
    [Modbus TCP]
    [MQTT]
    [Serial]
  }

  [Base Service] as BaseService

  note right of BaseService
    Source Protocol Adapters extend
    the base service class
  end note
  
SchemaRegistry --> BaseService
Instance --> BaseService : sample storage
}

note bottom of Service
**Service**
Runtime producer — process/module that connects to a data source or performs computations.
Managed by ProjectManager (start/stop lifecycle).
Can produce multiple streams.
**Stream**
Logical data channel from a service.
Registered in StreamRegistry with metadata (schema, rate, fidelity, etc.).
Can contain multiple signals (columns, metrics, channels).
**Signal**
Atomic data field within a stream — e.g., a single measurement, variable, or channel.
Examples:
temperature_stream → signals: temp_sensor1, temp_sensor2
high_fidelity_stream → signals: x_position, y_position, z_position
Signals share the same timestamp space within their stream.
end note

rectangle "Project Manager" as ProjectManager #LightSlateGrey {
  rectangle "Storage Manager" as StorageManager {
    ' Offline Storage Section
    package "Offline Storage" #LightCoral {
      [Offline Storage] as OfflineDataStorage

      interface "IStorageBackend" as IBackend
      note right of IBackend
        Pluggable backend interface
      end note

      component "Parquet Backend" as ParquetBackend #PaleGreen
      component "HDF5 Backend" as HDF5Backend #PaleTurquoise
      component "CSV Backend" as CSVBackend #Wheat
      component "Custom Backend" as CustomBackend #Lavender

      OfflineDataStorage -down-> IBackend : "uses"
      IBackend <|.. ParquetBackend
      IBackend <|.. HDF5Backend
      IBackend <|.. CSVBackend
      IBackend <|.. CustomBackend

      note bottom of ParquetBackend
        Zero-copy columnar writes
        via Arrow RecordBatch
      end note
    }

    ' Online Storage Section
    package "Online Storage" #LightYellow {
      collections "Stream Holders" as StreamHolders
      database "Stream Buffer" as StreamBuffer #WhiteSmoke {
        collections "Signal Buffer" as SignalBuffer
      }

      StreamHolders -> StreamBuffer
    }

  [Buffer Handle] as BufferHandle
  StreamBuffer -down-> BufferHandle
  }

  collections "Services" as services
}

note top of ProjectManager
ProjectManager
|_ Manages Stream Lifecycle (start/stop/configure)
|_ Stream Instance 1
  |_ Owns Service Instance A
  |_ Produces Signal Set α
  |_ Registers metadata → StreamRegistry
|_ Stream Instance 2
  |_ Owns Service Instance A (separate instance)
  |_ Produces Signal Set β
  |_ Registers metadata → StreamRegistry
|_ Stream Instance 3
  |_ Owns Service Instance B
  |_ Produces Signal Set γ
  |_ Registers metadata → StreamRegistry
|_ StreamRegistry
  |_ Stores stream + signal metadata
  |_ Emits events (stream started, signals available)
  |_ Notifies → StorageManager
    |_ Allocates buffers per stream
      |_ Buffers contain signals under schema
end note

rectangle "User Interface" {
  frame "Windows" as Windows #LightGreen {
    skinparam nodesep 0
    skinparam ranksep 0
    skinparam componentStyle rectangle
    [Signal Browser] as SignalBrowser
    [Live View] as LiveView
    [FPS] as FPS
    [Analysis View] as AnalysisView
    [Console] as Console

    Windows -right[hidden]-> SignalBrowser
    Windows -right[hidden]-> LiveView
    Windows -right[hidden]-> FPS
    Windows -right[hidden]-> AnalysisView
    Windows -right[hidden]-> Console
  }
}

Windows -left(0)-> ProjectManager : Open/Save Project
ProjectManager -(0)-> Service : Start/Stop Service
services -right[dashed]- Service

@enduml